{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8146a629-19f3-4ec8-93a6-671714cda82d","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01FJ7FDaaS3RfYBBpj7CZQus","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0162McN48cHTC5U2MkzeTYuQ","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-ebe6a0430b0d408b8da782cbb375b330 && dotnet nuget search xunit.v3 --take 5 2>/dev/null | head -30","description":"Search for xunit.v3 package","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Search for xunit.v3 package"}],"interactionId":"293e5d21-d15d-4acd-8acb-d9972a209562","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**: \n   - Replace `xunit` (v2) with `xunit.v3` (v3)\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't need it — tests are executables)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n   - Change SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` → add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` (v3 tests are executables)\n   - In v3, test projects become standalone executables with the entry point provided by the xunit.v3 package itself\n\n2. **DatabaseSetupAttribute.cs**:\n   - `BeforeAfterTestAttribute` still exists in v3 but moved to the `Xunit.v3` namespace with an updated signature where `Before` and `After` methods now accept `MethodInfo methodUnderTest` and `IXunitTest test` parameters\n   - Most core attributes like `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` remain in the `Xunit` namespace\n   - For `DatabaseTests.cs`, the using statements and attributes stay largely the same with minimal changes needed\n   - The `global.json` configuration should work with `dotnet test` since xUnit v3 has its own built-in test runner\n\n, though I should verify whether the VSTest runner setting needs to be removed or if it auto-detects properly\n\nNow I'm clarifying the core migration path for xUnit v3: switching from the `xunit` package to `xunit.v3`, removing the Visual Studio runner and test SDK dependencies, converting the project to an executable with the appropriate output type, and updating the `BeforeAfterTestAttribute` method signatures to accept the new parameters. I need to understand the xUnit v3 package structure and requirements before migrating—tests become executables rather than libraries, and the attribute signatures likely changed to accept the new `IXunitTest` parameter, so I'll install the package and verify the exact API.","outputTokens":1426,"requestId":"083D:1AA32E:8271D78:910DD13:69EACAE3"},"id":"c525ee3f-eabe-47fd-855d-7b60993ea92f","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:44:31.534Z","parentId":"2b7d5594-7598-4d8b-91b2-52df05585351"}
